text_Pegmatite: There are often large very black lines through the rock. Sometimes they are thick, other times they can be rice sized.
text_Peridotite: These are very speckled and come in a variety of colors. They are typically grey with some green at times. It usually has a light background with black, green, or red speckles.

text_Diorite: They come in a variety of colors, but typically are greyscale. There is a light background with black marbling. It almost looks like the old tv static.
text_Andesite: These are mostly grey rocks with small specks of either lighter or darker color. They tend to almost looks like they fossils in them.

text_Gabbro: These are mostly dark with some small discoloration in them. They are rough looking and are overwhelmed by the background color
text_Basalt: These are mostly greyscale and of one color. They appear uniform and clean with very little additional colors or markings in them.
